# https://example.org/mdr-ontology#ActionType
<https://example.org/mdr-ontology#ActionType> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class> .
<https://example.org/mdr-ontology#ActionType> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#subClassOf> <https://example.org/mdr-ontology#CorrectiveAction> .
<https://example.org/mdr-ontology#ActionType> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "A classification of corrective actions according to their nature or purpose, such as recall, safety alert, or in-situ correction." .
<https://example.org/mdr-ontology#ActionType> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Action Type" .
# 
# https://example.org/mdr-ontology#CorrectiveAction
<https://example.org/mdr-ontology#CorrectiveAction> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class> .
<https://example.org/mdr-ontology#CorrectiveAction> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "An action taken to eliminate or reduce the risk associated with a medical device incident." .
<https://example.org/mdr-ontology#CorrectiveAction> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Corrective Action" .
# 
# https://example.org/mdr-ontology#CorrectiveActionStatus
<https://example.org/mdr-ontology#CorrectiveActionStatus> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class> .
<https://example.org/mdr-ontology#CorrectiveActionStatus> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#subClassOf> <https://example.org/mdr-ontology#CorrectiveAction> .
<https://example.org/mdr-ontology#CorrectiveActionStatus> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "The current state of a corrective action, indicating whether it is open, ongoing, or closed." .
<https://example.org/mdr-ontology#CorrectiveActionStatus> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Status" .
# 
# https://example.org/mdr-ontology#Device
<https://example.org/mdr-ontology#Device> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class> .
<https://example.org/mdr-ontology#Device> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#subClassOf> _:genid4 .
