<https://example.org/mdr-ontology#Device> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "A medical device regulated under MDR or IVDR, including implantable, active or diagnostic devices." .
<https://example.org/mdr-ontology#Device> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Device" .
# 
# https://example.org/mdr-ontology#DeviceType
<https://example.org/mdr-ontology#DeviceType> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class> .
<https://example.org/mdr-ontology#DeviceType> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#subClassOf> <https://example.org/mdr-ontology#Device> .
<https://example.org/mdr-ontology#DeviceType> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "A classification that describes the functional or structural characteristics of a medical device, such as implantable or active." .
<https://example.org/mdr-ontology#DeviceType> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Device Type" .
# 
# https://example.org/mdr-ontology#Incident
<https://example.org/mdr-ontology#Incident> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class> .
<https://example.org/mdr-ontology#Incident> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "An event involving a medical device that may lead to or has led to harm, malfunction or safety issues." .
<https://example.org/mdr-ontology#Incident> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Incident" .
# 
# https://example.org/mdr-ontology#IncidentType
<https://example.org/mdr-ontology#IncidentType> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class> .
<https://example.org/mdr-ontology#IncidentType> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#subClassOf> <https://example.org/mdr-ontology#Incident> .
<https://example.org/mdr-ontology#IncidentType> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "A categorization of incidents based on their severity or nature, such as serious incident or near-miss." .
<https://example.org/mdr-ontology#IncidentType> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Incident Type" .
# 
# https://example.org/mdr-ontology#Manufacturer
<https://example.org/mdr-ontology#Manufacturer> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class> .
<https://example.org/mdr-ontology#Manufacturer> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "An organization responsible for designing, manufacturing or placing a medical device on the market." .
<https://example.org/mdr-ontology#Manufacturer> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Manufacturer" .
# 
# https://example.org/mdr-ontology#ProbabilityLevel
<https://example.org/mdr-ontology#ProbabilityLevel> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class> .
<https://example.org/mdr-ontology#ProbabilityLevel> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#subClassOf> <https://example.org/mdr-ontology#Risk> .
<https://example.org/mdr-ontology#ProbabilityLevel> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "A classification indicating the likelihood of occurrence of a risk, typically expressed as low, medium, or high." .
<https://example.org/mdr-ontology#ProbabilityLevel> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Probability Level" .
# 
# https://example.org/mdr-ontology#RegulatoryFramework
<https://example.org/mdr-ontology#RegulatoryFramework> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class> .
<https://example.org/mdr-ontology#RegulatoryFramework> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#subClassOf> <https://example.org/mdr-ontology#Device> .
<https://example.org/mdr-ontology#RegulatoryFramework> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "A regulatory classification that determines the legal framework applicable to a medical device, such as MDR or IVDR." .
<https://example.org/mdr-ontology#RegulatoryFramework> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Regulatory Framework" .
# 
# https://example.org/mdr-ontology#Risk
<https://example.org/mdr-ontology#Risk> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class> .
<https://example.org/mdr-ontology#Risk> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "A potential source of harm associated with the use or malfunction of a medical device." .
<https://example.org/mdr-ontology#Risk> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Risk" .
# 
# https://example.org/mdr-ontology#RiskCategory
<https://example.org/mdr-ontology#RiskCategory> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class> .
<https://example.org/mdr-ontology#RiskCategory> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#subClassOf> <https://example.org/mdr-ontology#Risk> .
<https://example.org/mdr-ontology#RiskCategory> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "A high-level classification of risks based on their origin, such as device-related or patient-related risks." .
<https://example.org/mdr-ontology#RiskCategory> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Category" .
# 
# https://example.org/mdr-ontology#RiskClass
<https://example.org/mdr-ontology#RiskClass> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class> .
<https://example.org/mdr-ontology#RiskClass> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#subClassOf> <https://example.org/mdr-ontology#Device> .
<https://example.org/mdr-ontology#RiskClass> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "A classification indicating the level of regulatory risk associated with a device, typically based on safety and intended use." .
<https://example.org/mdr-ontology#RiskClass> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Risk Class" .
# 
# https://example.org/mdr-ontology#SeverityLevel
<https://example.org/mdr-ontology#SeverityLevel> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class> .
<https://example.org/mdr-ontology#SeverityLevel> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#subClassOf> <https://example.org/mdr-ontology#Risk> .
<https://example.org/mdr-ontology#SeverityLevel> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "A classification indicating the potential impact or seriousness of a risk, such as minor, serious, or critical." .
<https://example.org/mdr-ontology#SeverityLevel> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Severity Level" .
# 
# https://example.org/mdr-ontology#riskType
<https://example.org/mdr-ontology#riskType> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class> .
<https://example.org/mdr-ontology#riskType> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#subClassOf> <https://example.org/mdr-ontology#Risk> .
<https://example.org/mdr-ontology#riskType> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "A more specific classification of risks within a category, describing the nature of the hazard, such as infection or mechanical failure." .
<https://example.org/mdr-ontology#riskType> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Type" .
